# Onterra Landing Page - Project Architecture

## Project Overview

This is a Next.js 15 + Sanity CMS project for Onterra Real Estate Investment Firm. Every aspect of the website should be editable through Sanity CMS.

## Core Principles

- **Sanity-First**: All content must be manageable through Sanity CMS
- **Component-Driven**: Build small, reusable, scalable components
- **Production Quality**: Enterprise-level code standards
- **Type Safety**: Full TypeScript implementation
- **Performance**: Optimized for Core Web Vitals

## Technology Stack

- **Framework**: Next.js 15 with App Router
- **CMS**: Sanity 4.6.1 (Project ID: jkbyd2en)
- **Styling**: Tailwind CSS 4 with OKLCH colors
- **UI**: Shadcn UI components only
- **State**: Jotai + TanStack Query
- **Language**: TypeScript 5 (strict mode)

## File Structure

```
src/
├── app/                    # Next.js App Router
├── components/            # Reusable components
│   ├── ui/               # Shadcn UI components (DO NOT EDIT)
│   ├── content/          # Sanity content components
│   ├── layout/           # Layout components
│   └── forms/            # Form components
├── lib/
│   ├── sanity/           # Sanity configuration
│   └── utils/            # Utility functions
├── hooks/                # Custom React hooks
└── sanity/               # Sanity schemas and utilities
```

## Development Workflow

- **Simultaneous Development**: Next.js dev server + Sanity Studio
- **Studio Access**: Available at `/studio` route
- **Content Management**: All content editable through Sanity Studio
- **Type Generation**: Auto-generate types from Sanity schemas
